<ReportItem port="9200" svc_name="www" protocol="tcp" severity="1" pluginID="83875" pluginName="SSL/TLS Diffie-Hellman Modulus &lt;= 1024 Bits (Logjam)" pluginFamily="Misc.">
<bid>74733</bid>
<cea-id>CEA-2021-0004</cea-id>
<cpe>cpe:/a:openssl:openssl</cpe>
<cve>CVE-2015-4000</cve>
<cvss3_base_score>3.7</cvss3_base_score>
<cvss3_temporal_score>3.2</cvss3_temporal_score>
<cvss3_temporal_vector>CVSS:3.0/E:U/RL:O/RC:C</cvss3_temporal_vector>
<cvss3_vector>CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:L/A:N</cvss3_vector>
<cvss_base_score>2.6</cvss_base_score>
<cvss_score_rationale>An in depth analysis by Tenable researchers revealed the Access Complexity to be high.</cvss_score_rationale>
<cvss_score_source>manual</cvss_score_source>
<cvss_temporal_score>1.9</cvss_temporal_score>
<cvss_temporal_vector>CVSS2#E:U/RL:OF/RC:C</cvss_temporal_vector>
<cvss_vector>CVSS2#AV:N/AC:H/Au:N/C:N/I:P/A:N</cvss_vector>
<description>The remote host allows SSL/TLS connections with one or more Diffie-Hellman moduli less than or equal to 1024 bits. Through cryptanalysis, a third party may be able to find the shared secret in a short amount of time (depending on modulus size and attacker resources). This may allow an attacker to recover the plaintext or potentially violate the integrity of connections.</description>
<epss_score>0.939</epss_score>
<exploitability_ease>No known exploits are available</exploitability_ease>
<fname>ssl_logjam.nasl</fname>
<in_the_news>true</in_the_news>
<plugin_modification_date>2025/12/15</plugin_modification_date>
<plugin_name>SSL/TLS Diffie-Hellman Modulus &lt;= 1024 Bits (Logjam)</plugin_name>
<plugin_publication_date>2015/05/28</plugin_publication_date>
<plugin_type>remote</plugin_type>
<risk_factor>Low</risk_factor>
<script_version>1.42</script_version>
<see_also>https://weakdh.org/</see_also>
<solution>Reconfigure the service to use a unique Diffie-Hellman moduli of 2048 bits or greater.</solution>
<synopsis>The remote host allows SSL/TLS connections with one or more Diffie-Hellman moduli less than or equal to 1024 bits.</synopsis>
<thorough_tests>true</thorough_tests>
