<ReportItem port="9200" svc_name="www" protocol="tcp" severity="0" pluginID="51080" pluginName="Web Server Uses Basic Authentication over HTTPS" pluginFamily="Web Servers">
<description>The remote web server contains web pages that are protected by &apos;Basic&apos; authentication over HTTPS. 

While this is not in itself a security flaw, in some organizations, the use of &apos;Basic&apos; authentication is discouraged as, depending on the underlying implementation, it may be vulnerable to account brute-forcing or may encourage Man-in-The-Middle (MiTM) attacks.</description>
<fname>www_https_basic_authentication.nasl</fname>
<plugin_modification_date>2011/03/18</plugin_modification_date>
